<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Working with Data Visualizations</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>The user interface for monitoring your services and virtual machines integrates with Grafana, an open source application for visualizing large-scale monitoring data on metrics dashboards. <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> ships with preconfigured dashboards for Monitoring Service and OpenStack operators. As an application operator, you can configure your own dashboard as required. </p>
            <p>To access the functions for configuring a dashboard, use the options at the top border of the <uicontrol>Overview</uicontrol> page. This allows you to access Grafana and you can instantly start creating your dashboard for the metrics data you want to visualize.</p>
            <p>Dashboard example:</p>
            <fig>
                <image alt="grafana-libvirt.png" height="260" href="../../images/grafana-libvirt.png" width="435"/>
            </fig>
        </section>
